name: Bali Jungle Taksu
address: Jln Subak Jasan Jl. Br Jasan, Sebatu, Kec. Tegallalang, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80561, Indonesia
review 1: My wife and I have vacationed to Bali from Canada for the past two years. We stayed at the Taksu Bali Jungle villa and highly recommend to anyone looking for the best villa for relaxation and experience the jungle. The workers miss Koman and Rani are amazing! They come and cook your meals in the outside kitchen and are so respectful of your privacy. They are in and out before you know it. The best experience!
review 2: It's really nice room with amazing view, sometime in the morning i always hear bird sound its make me feel fresh and amazing day for me to do activity like yoga to refresh my mind
review 3: This place is the most magical experience we have had in bali!!! This is not just a villa it is a beautiful treehouse type of experience! Beautifully kept, clean with every little detail thought through!!! Yoga mats, hammock, umbrellas, full kitchen and the staff.... Koman,  Rani, DeAda and all his amazing drivers treated us like kings and queens. This is our second year staying (first year at the Merta House and this year at Taksu Jungle) both are an unforgettable experience!
review 4: Beautiful place! Cozy comfortable villa! It's Very quiet and calm! Complete unity with nature. You can go down to the river and swim. I'll come back here again.
review 5: Marvelous place in the jungle, very calm and peaceful. Close to the waterfall and near the rice terraces. Totally recommended.
